                <pb facs="1037" n="1013" xml:id="pg_1013"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">I <hi rend="italic">Hearing of the Yugoslav and Italian
                        Representatives</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The hearing of the Yugoslav and Italian representatives, decided upon at the
                    previous meeting of the Council, was fixed for November 6 at 10:30 a.m.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II <hi rend="italic">Recommendations of the Paris Conference on
                        the Draft Peace Treaty With Italy</hi>
                    <note n="39" xml:id="d299fn39">
                        <ref target="frus1946v04#pg_889">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                            889</ref>. The location of specific articles cited in this section are
                        indicated in annotations to the United States Delegation Minutes, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 64, Part B, Para. 3</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council considered the addition proposed by the Australian Delegation to
                    Article 64, Part B, Paragraph 3. It was <hi rend="italic">decided</hi> that the
                    Deputies should study this question on the basis of the following new proposal
                    presented by M. Couve de Murville:</p>
                <p>Add to Paragraph 6, Part B, Article 64, the words: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The four Ambassadors, in consultation with the heads of the Diplomatic
                            Missions of the interested countries, shall coordinate and control the
                            application of the provisions of Part B of the present Article.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The U.K. representative reserved his position on the above proposal until it had
                    been studied in relation to Articles 72, 75, and 76.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 64, Part C. Special provisions for earlier
                        deliveries</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The U.K. representative withdrew his objections to this recommendation which was
                    accordingly <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi> by the Council.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 67, Para. 2, Transfer of German assets in Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The U.S.S.R. representative withdrew his objections to this recommendation which
                    was accordingly <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi> by the Council.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 68, Para. 4. Compensation for damages to United
                        Nations property in Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision of this paragraph was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 69, sub-paragraph</hi> (<hi rend="italic">e</hi>)</p>
                <p>Sub-paragraph (<hi rend="italic">e</hi>) was <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi> by
                    the Council, the U.S. Delegation having agreed to accept the Paris Conference
                    recommendation.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 71, Paragraph 1</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views on the various recommendations and proposals, a
                    decision on this paragraph was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 72, Settlement of economic disputes</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 74</hi> (<hi rend="italic">A</hi>), <hi rend="italic">Waiver by Italy of her participation in the International Financial
                        Commission in Greece</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The U.S.S.R. Delegation was in favor of rejecting this recommendation. The U.K.
                    and French Delegations, while raising no objection in principle to rejection,
                    asked for consideration of this proposal to be postponed until they had
                    consulted with one another on the subject.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 76, Settlement of disputes concerning the
                        interpretation and execution of the Treaty</hi>
                </p>
                <pb facs="1038" n="1014" xml:id="pg_1014"/>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 77</hi>, (<hi rend="italic">A</hi>), (<hi rend="italic">New Article</hi>)</p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting of the Council</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Wednesday, November 6, at 10:30 a.m.</p>
